4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section, "emergency action plan":
6 (a) Has the same meaning as in 29 C.F.R. sec. 1910.38; and
7 (b) Means the procedures and rules to follow in the event of fire, natural
8 disaster, or other threatening situation that may pose a health or safety
9 hazard to the employees in the workplace.
10 (2) (a) Each employer shall create an emergency action plan. The plan shall be
11 written, kept in the workplace, and available for employees for review.
12 (b) For employers with ten (10) or fewer employees, the emergency action plan
13 does not need to be written and may be communicated orally to employees.
14 (3) An emergency action plan shall include at a minimum:
15 (a) Procedures for employees to report a fire or other emergency;
16 (b) Procedures for emergency evacuation, including the type of evacuation and
17 exit route assignments;
18 (c) Procedures to be followed by employees who remain at the workplace to
19 operate critical plant operations before evacuating;
20 (d) Procedures to account for all employees after an evacuation;
21 (e) Procedures to be followed by employees who perform rescue or medical
22 duties; and
23 (f) The name or job title of every employee who may be contacted by an
24 employee who needs more information about the plan or an explanation of
25 his or her duties under the plan.
26 (4) Each employer shall establish and maintain an employee alarm system. The
27 employee alarm system shall have a distinctive signal for each purpose and
